<br>
RP doesn't require a funny speech pattern (though some RPers use that as a way to express their character's difference from themselves or even to give their character a bit more... flair) or thees and thous (though that could be used to define someone of the gentry or who sees himself as gentry or someone a bit more &quot;refined&quot;) or even using a made-up language from an entirely different game (many who use it do so to give a different bit of accent and flair in exactly the same way as those who type the sound of their character or who use thees and thous), though a speech pattern does make it evident when RP is dropped for what ever reason.   It doesn't require writing elaborate stories as or about your character (though some do as a way to continue their character out of game or to bridge things in game and give the character more depth or simply because they like to write stories).  It doesn't even require seeing one race/class or group of races/classes as wrong (though many do as a way to differentiate their character from themselves) and calling others names or not helping them.<br>
<br>
Your character doesn't know about Monday night football, he doesn't know about the latest movie or music video, he might know about how much damage he can output, he probably knows how this or that spell effect him, he probaly even has a different understanding of death since he gets a free trip to the soul binder when it happens, he probably also does know how things, like himself, reappear after a time or three and that others might have knowledge on the timing, and he most definately knows that killing things in certain places can advance his own carrer or line his pocket pretty well or might take a huge organised force (yes, even grinding for XP or cash can be integrated into RP as can raiding).<br>
<br>
Those who say they are casual RPers or don't RP much but express things as their character would (even abreviations such as SoW and KEI) even giving the character a &quot;life&quot; similar to their own and don't laugh at those who do use speech patterns (except <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>as their character might laugh at them</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->) are RPing. If they are consitent, they might even be a better RPer than the person who is writing elaborate tales, or using a speech pattern.  RP is simply interactive storytelling.<br>
<br>
All I could ask of someone coming here is that they not talk like a warez d00d (unless they are trying to portray an idiot, perhaps, with a very messed up way of talking), and not say &quot;dude, u RPers r so funny&quot; or the like and give even &quot;casual&quot; RP a shot, look a the world through your character's eyes instead of your own and leave the 21-century-isms alone.<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh... and one last thing.  RP is not standing against ebaying, server transfers, the change in ruleset, other changes SOE has decided to impose on the server, or growling about the increasing number of d00ds and those antagonistic to RP (specifically those who go out of their way to mock RPers or even exclude them).  That is an OOC stance and might well be in support of ones desire to RP and a view that these are the antithesis of RP.  These things that one might stand against don't stop the RP, but for many of us they do make it harder because RPing alone is pretty pointless since it leaves out the interactive part.  These things can also change the setting which makes the RP out of place and jarring even to the one RPing like a portrayal of Romeo and Juliette using the words written by Shakespeare but set in modern day New York, you know it doesn't fit.<br>
<br>
I am against ebaying (or any in-game use of Real World money aside from buying the software and paying for the account(s)) more because of I see it as the antithesis of RP than because of the EULA (though SOE has broken their contract with us, so why keep our contract with them?) because it is an incursion of this modern world into the fabric of the game.  I am against cross server transfers because of the threat of the arrival of even more who are anti-RP but at higher levels and because it will likely make more use of ebaying and because they have no reason (even less so than others) to have any respect for the community of FV or the RPers.  Yes, I am well aware that some who have bought characters or transferred are RPers and good people behind them.  Yes, I am aware that some who have sold characters are RPers and have good people behind them and have, in their own mind, justified why they sold.  It doesn't mean I have to agree with their actions even if I can accept the person as fine.  It doesn't mean I have to respect that choice or even accept/respect the justification for it.<br>
<br>
I put this in the soapbox because I did bring up the &quot;HOT&quot; topics at the end and know it could draw flames.  But, this is not a rant, jsut an opinion. <br>
<br>
