<br>
Roleplaying isn't necessarily much.<br>
<br>
One person in my guild told me he doesn't roleplay.  I answered him, why then did he love to suicide his one character, and not the other?  That's roleplay too, giving your character a &quot;quirk&quot;.<br>
<br>
Pretty simple, if you got more than one character and find yourself treating them differently... you are roleplaying.<br>
<br>
It doesn't need to be different from you.  Your character can be conniving or honest... just like you.  *shrugs*<br>
<br>
What's not roleplaying is talking non-eq terms.<br>
<br>
Things like discussing various stats and strategies of EQ are part of the game. I may tire of them in a long discussion but I wouldn't consider those entirely out of character. After all, my character is used to armor showing &quot;stats&quot;. I choose to take the world of EQ as it is, not trying too hard to fit it into what the real world is like (after all, in the real world, you only die once, there are no zones, and the /follow command doesn't work...)<br>
<br>
Talking about latest wars in RL, or politics, or who won last night's basketball game... that's OOC and definitely not stuff  a fantasy character would know about.<br>
<br>
<br>
*doesn't touch ebaying with even a 10 foot pole*<br>
