<br>
For example.  Falcolas is, in game terms, an agnostic bard.  He, again by game terms, sings and follows no god.  In his RP life, though... he does not sing (in fact is a horrible singer), he hums.  He has given his swords Tunare.  The game is too limited in scope - again in my opinion - to encompass who my characters are when they roleplay.<br>
<br>
So, decisions I make in the game, purchasing PP or transferring my character - simply do not affect how I roleplay my character.  Large changes, like the transfer, must be roleplayed out to preserve continuity in the character, however... it honestly does not affect who my character is, merely with whom and where he can interact.<br>
<br>
But - thank you for talking this through - your own views had me confused, until I realized we look at the game itself very differently. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=318126">Falcolas Swiftsong</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
